      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., E% or MAPE) on hemolysis index must be computed with uncertainty bounds for all 5 operating points; statistical comparison must account for experimental repeatability.",
      "rationale": "MAPE on hemolysis index is 18% averaged across operating points. Uncertainty bounds are computed via Monte Carlo but experimental repeatability data covers only 3 of 5 operating points. Achieved level 4 is below required level 5."
