      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, fluid, and operating envelope as the COU; any geometric or fluid differences must be bounded by sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA generic pump geometry which matches the COU geometry. Fluid is bovine blood rather than human blood; a sensitivity study on viscosity differences is provided but does not cover hematocrit variability. Achieved level 4 is below required level 5."
